<span class="bigTitle">Why do YOU deserve a trip to the finals in San Diego?</span>
<br><br>
Did you miss out on making it as a TCCC finalist?  Still want to see the finals in San Diego anyway?  Here's your chance!
<br><br>
<span class="bodySubtitle">The contest:</span><br/>
Write to us and tell us why you'd be a good candidate to come to San Diego and blog about the 2006 TopCoder&#174; Collegiate Challenge, Sponsored by AOL&#174;.  We want two bloggers to join us at the finals and give a member's perspective on the competition, the atmosphere, and the city.  You'll win a trip to San Diego, as well as have your blog posted on the TCCC website for everyone to read.  
<br><br>
<span class="bigTitle">Who can compete:</span><br/>
In order to be eligible, you must be a registered TopCoder member who is 18 years of age or older as of November 14, 2006.  In addition, you must have competed in either three (3) SRMs or passed review in one (1) component competition by October 16 to be eligible to win. 
<br><br>
<span class="bigTitle">How it will work:</span><br/>
Email your story to TopCoder at <A href="mailto:pickme@topcoder.com">pickme@topcoder.com</A>.  TopCoder staff will read through the submissions and choose the two members they think are most deserving of the trip.  The winning submissions will be featured in the TCCC06 program and on the TopCoder website.  
<br><br>
<span class="bigTitle">What you get:</span><br/>
The winning submission-holders win an expenses-paid trip to San Diego, including airfare, hotel and meals paid for by TopCoder.    
<br><br>
<span class="bigTitle">Important dates:</span><br/>
Submit your story now!  The deadline for submission is Monday, October 16, 2006, at 5:00 PM EDT.  Submissions received after that time will not be considered.  The lucky winners will be announced on the website and via email on October 17, 2006.  
<br><br>
<span class="bigTitle">Rules:</span><br/>
Each eligible member may make only one submission.  Submissions must meet the following criteria to be considered:
<ul>
<li>Submission must be 500 words or less</li>
<li>Submission must be written in English</li>
<li>Submission must be text only with no photos or URLs.</li>
<li>Submission must be written inside the body of an email.  No attachments are allowed.</li>
<li>Submissions must be anonymous.  No handles or references to your name can be made in any way in your submission.</li>
</ul>

The winners must be able to travel to San Diego, California, USA from November 14 - November 18, 2006.  If the selected winners do not possess the necessary documents and/or visas to travel to the U.S. as of October 18, 2006, TopCoder will select another winner(s).
